message.content:
You are not a prime number because you mentioned that you're "one more than a square number." We can look at the squares of numbers between 20 and 40, find the one more than each square, and see which one applies to you:

Squares between 20 and 40:
- 20^2 = 400
- 21^2 = 441
- 22^2 = 484
- 23^2 = 529
- 24^2 = 576
- 25^2 = 625
- 26^2 = 676
- 27^2 = 729
- 28^2 = 784
- 29^2 = 841
- 30^2 = 900
- 31^2 = 961
- 32^2 = 1024
- 33^2 = 1089
- 34^2 = 1156
- 35^2 = 1225
- 36^2 = 1296
- 37^2 = 1369
- 38^2 = 1444
- 39^2 = 1521
- 40^2 = 1600

Since you are one more than the square, your number is either:
- 21^2 + 1 = 441 + 1 = 442 (prime)
- 22^2 + 1 = 484 + 1 = 485 (not prime)
- 23^2 + 1 = 529 + 1 = 530 (not prime)
- 24^2 + 1 = 576 + 1 = 577 (not prime)
- 25^2 + 1 = 625 + 1 = 626 (not prime)
- 26^2 + 1 = 676 + 1 = 677 (not prime)
- 27^2 + 1 = 729 + 1 = 730 (not prime)
- 28^2 + 1 = 784 + 1 = 785 (not prime)
- 29^2 + 1 = 841 + 1 = 842 (prime)
- 30^2 + 1 = 900 + 1 = 901 (not prime)
- 31^2 + 1 = 961 + 1 = 962 (not prime)
- 32^2 + 1 = 1024 + 1 = 1025 (not prime)
- 33^2 + 1 = 1089 + 1 = 1090 (not prime)
- 34^2 + 1 = 1156 + 1 = 1157 (not prime)
- 35^2 + 1 = 1225 + 1 = 1226 (not prime)
- 36^2 + 1 = 1296 + 1 = 1297 (not prime)
- 37^2 + 1 = 1369 + 1 = 1370 (not prime)
- 38^2 + 1 = 1444 + 1 = 1445 (not prime)
- 39^2 + 1 = 1521 + 1 = 1522 (not prime)
- 40^2 + 1 = 1600 + 1 = 1601 (not prime)

Based on this, you could be either 442 (prime) or 29^2 + 1 = 842 (also prime).
